WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:06.690 --> 00:00:06.880
[Music]

00:00:06.880 --> 00:00:09.730
This is Fieldsports Channel News.

00:00:09.730 --> 00:00:15.700
Sports stars are getting different reactions
to their hunting exploits all over the world.

00:00:15.700 --> 00:00:21.699
New Zealand rugby players Tom Taylor, George
and Sam Whitelock, Ben Funnell and Tyler Bleyendaal

00:00:21.699 --> 00:00:26.930
have been attacked by antis for posting pictures
of themselves hunting big game while out on

00:00:26.930 --> 00:00:28.370
tour in South Africa.

00:00:28.370 --> 00:00:33.300
The antis say this is part of their campaign
against canned hunting, even though the rugby

00:00:33.300 --> 00:00:36.360
players were not on a canned hunt.

00:00:36.360 --> 00:00:42.379
Meanwhile, American Olympic wrestler Dremiel
Byers has been hit with a ‘wildlife violations’

00:00:42.379 --> 00:00:42.899
rap.

00:00:42.899 --> 00:00:47.489
The 10-time national champion wrestler was
spotted hunting a whitetail deer with a bow

00:00:47.489 --> 00:00:52.719
and arrow in the parking lot of Lexus dealership
in Colorado.

00:00:52.719 --> 00:00:57.319
And American football quarterback Stephen
McGee is getting plaudits in his native Texas

00:00:57.319 --> 00:01:04.319
for starring in a new hunting TV show alongside
his wife Brittany. It is called The Camo Life.

00:01:04.930 --> 00:01:11.700
James Purdey &amp; Sons have created a trio of
guns to mark the bicentenary year of 2014

00:01:11.700 --> 00:01:14.030
– and they are for sale now.

00:01:14.030 --> 00:01:19.350
The two shotguns and one .470 Express double
rifle with oak and leather travel case and

00:01:19.350 --> 00:01:26.350
custom-built glass display case are for sale
by sealed bids, closing the 19 December 2014.

00:01:26.530 --> 00:01:31.460
The winning bidder will be informed of their
success in writing by Friday 16 January 2015.

00:01:31.460 --> 00:01:36.730
Some of the proceeds will go to The Prince’s
Trust and some to The Gunmakers’ Company

00:01:36.730 --> 00:01:39.020
Charitable Trust

00:01:39.020 --> 00:01:44.380
Shooters in Malta will be gathering on a church
rooftop and shooting shotguns into the air.

00:01:44.380 --> 00:01:50.520
The ceremony takes place on 31 August on the
parish church in St Julians. St Julian the

00:01:50.520 --> 00:01:55.390
Hospitaller is also a patron saint of hunters.
The Maltese hunters, who are under fire for

00:01:55.390 --> 00:02:00.050
shooting migratory birds will use blank cartridges.

00:02:00.050 --> 00:02:04.909
Chinese internet titan Jack Ma has hit out
at a British report that he indulged in a

00:02:04.909 --> 00:02:10.729
luxurious British hunting trip. He says that
shooting trip was for animal conservation,

00:02:10.729 --> 00:02:12.390
not recreation.

00:02:12.390 --> 00:02:17.030
The Chinese Nature Conservancy also defended
Ma, a director on the organisation's board,

00:02:17.030 --> 00:02:21.310
after Britain's The Sunday Times reported
on Sunday that billionaire Ma was among the

00:02:21.310 --> 00:02:25.010
Chinese new rich indulging in upmarket hunting
trips in Britain.

00:02:25.010 --> 00:02:30.010
The report in the South China Morning Post
says more of China's moneyed classes are spending

00:02:30.010 --> 00:02:35.590
big on hunting in Britain to emulate the aristocratic
lifestyle depicted in British television shows

00:02:35.590 --> 00:02:41.590
shown on Chinese TV such as Downton Abbey
and Fieldsports Channel. Don't you know.

00:02:41.590 --> 00:02:47.340
And finally, a YouTube film shows a man swimming
for his life when he is pursued by a crocodile.

00:02:47.340 --> 00:02:52.740
He is swimming to a nearby shore as the predator
closes in on him. An onlooker has the presence

00:02:52.740 --> 00:02:57.180
of mind to hurl an object from the jetty and
the splash is enough to send the crocodile

00:02:57.180 --> 00:03:00.440
swimming off in the other direction.

00:03:00.440 --> 00:03:02.520
You are now up to date with Fieldsports Channel
News.

00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:05.010
